{"word":"G2168 - εὐχαριστέω - eucharistéō - yoo-khar-is-teh'-o - Thank","slug":"G2168","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">εὐχαριστέω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>eucharistéō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>yoo-khar-is-teh'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Thank"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"- Original: <b><el>εὐχαριστέω</el></b> <p />- Transliteration: <b>Eucharisteo</b> <p />- Phonetic: <b>yoo-khar-is-teh'-o</b> <p class=\"def\">- Definition: </p> <p class='li260'><b>1.</b> to be grateful, feel thankful </p> <p class='li260'><b>2.</b> give thanks </p> <p class=\"origin\"/>- Origin: from <a href=\"#/G2170\">G2170</a> <p />- TDNT entry: 15:47,1 <p />- Part(s) of speech: Verb <p />- Strong's: From <a href=\"#/G2170\">G2170</a>; to <i>be grateful</i> that is (actually) to <i>express gratitude</i> (towards); specifically to <i>say grace</i> at a <b>meal</b>: - (give) thank (-ful -s). "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G2169\">G2169</a>, <a href=\"#/G2170\">G2170</a>, <a href=\"#/G4796\">G4796</a>, <a href=\"#/G5463\">G5463</a>, <a href=\"#/G5479\">G5479</a>, <a href=\"#/G5483\">G5483</a>, <a href=\"#/G5484\">G5484</a>, <a href=\"#/G5485\">G5485</a>, <a href=\"#/G5486\">G5486</a>, <a href=\"#/G5487\">G5487</a>, <a href=\"#/G884\">G884</a>"}]}